This can also be applied to the PowerSoil Pro Kit.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8em33","text":"Use this protocol for Low Biomass or high contamination samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1cstb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dbu6c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"4je4n","text":"Using some small tweaks to an already optimized protocol you can get your DNA from contaminated samples!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"7eulr","text":"DNeasy Powersoil Kit (Adjusted name to PowerLyzer Kit) - https://www.qiagen.com/us/products/discovery-and-translational-research/dna-rna-purification/dna-purification/microbial-dna/dneasy-powerlyzer-powersoil-kit/","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":57,"length":156}],"data":{}},{"key":"79rda","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bmcm","text":"DNeasy Powersoil Pro Kit https://www.qiagen.com/us/products/discovery-and-translational-research/dna-rna-purification/dna-purification/microbial-dna/dneasy-powersoil-pro-kit/","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":25,"length":149}],"data":{}},{"key":"blkhr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b11rk","text":"100% ethanol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"BC502240352311ED98330A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.qiagen.com/us/products/discovery-and-translational-research/dna-rna-purification/dna-purification/microbial-dna/dneasy-powerlyzer-powersoil-kit"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"A08E838C352311ED98330A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.qiagen.com/us/products/discovery-and-translational-research/dna-rna-purification/dna-purification/microbial-dna/dneasy-powersoil-pro-kit"}}}}

status.info: We used this protocol on tar contaminated soil and worked great! Got good Illumina data for 16S and ITS1.

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7m6ha","text":"Add sample into the PowerBead tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1md5k","text":"Add 60μL of Solution C1. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"824of","text":"Make sure the sample has not precipitated. If so, heat sample to 60ºC until precipitate is dissolved into solution. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3sjte","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2i9tt","text":"Vortex to mix and incubate at 65ºC for 10 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dl541","text":"Bead beat at \"homogenize\" setting: 90 seconds bead beating, 60 seconds rest, then another 90 seconds (3 minutes total of actual beating).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ba86o","text":"Centrifuge at 10,000 x g for 30 s.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5hf6f","text":"Remove the supernatant or upper aqueous layer if you have one, to the new tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"buimi","text":"Add 100 uL Solution C2 and 100μL of Solution C3. Vortex to mix. Incubate at 4ºC or on ice for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fpk15","text":"*This is for low humic soils (100μL of each). If high humic soil, add 150μL C2 followed by 150μL C3.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e6kcd","text":"Centrifuge to pellet (1 min at 10,000 x g.) and transfer the supernatant to a new tube. Avoid pellet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e1mgk","text":"Ideally you will have 650μL of lysate, and can add 650μL of Solution C4 and 650μL of 100% ethanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"93sj0","text":"If you have 700μL, add 700μL of Solution C4 and 600μL of 100% ethanol. (Keep it as close to 1:1 as possible)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ee4e8","text":"Load the lysate to the spin filter 650μL at a time and bind in three steps, alternating with centrifugation (1 min at 10,000 x g). Discard flow-through each time.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5jkj5","text":"Make sure you mix C4 solution well. If new kit add ethanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6561l","text":"If the membrane is not stained brown, wash with 650μL of 100% ethanol (centrifuge 1 min at 10,000 x g and discard flow-through).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"56uh0","text":"If the membrane is stained brown, per sample, prepare a mix of 300μL of Solution C4 and 370μL of 100%","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bks8","text":"ethanol. Wash the column with this mixture first. Follow this wash with the 100% ethanol wash.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"64cgq","text":"Wash with 500μL of solution C5 (centrifuge 1 min at 10,000 x g and discard flow-through)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"85boh","text":"Dry the spin column for 2 minutes 10,000 x g. Transfer to a clean tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2kpc8","text":"Elute in 60μL of buffer C6 (Heat this buffer to 60ºC before eluting). Let the buffer sit on the membrane 5","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"df1g2","text":"minutes before elution. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8jr2s","text":"Then centrifuge for 1 min 10,000 x g into your storage tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
